Minecraft Bedrock fixes for macOS

Step 1. Download the Nightly build from here:
https://github.com/minecraft-linux/macos-builder/releases

Step 2. Open the launcher onetime then close it.
Step 3. Copy this file to this location:
profiles.ini
/Users/{your-mac-username}/Library/Application Support/mcpelauncher/profiles
Step 4. Open the Launcher in dev mode and check these settings:
Step 5. Launch Minecraft.

Note: I have had best results always running the lanucher in dev mode

Simple script to do that:

#!/bin/bash
open -a /Applications/Minecraft\ Bedrock\ Launcher.app/ --args -d
exit 0
